**Abstract:** Paper dated January 1992 titled "Narrative and Statement" examining the epistemological shift from narrative to propositional theology in the 12th-13th centuries. Argues that Aquinas's Summa represents a fundamental departure from patristic theology by mediating faith through Aristotelian epistemology. Contrasts Augustine's practical, experiential approach with Aquinas's theoretical, systematic method. Includes extensive notes on Aristotle's Nicomachean Ethics regarding speculative vs. practical rationality.
**AI Recommendation:** HIGH - Major theoretical document synthesizing Monasterio's critique of scholastic theology with his reading of Aristotle; essential for understanding the historical-philosophical argument of his work.

